## THE HOWRIE INDICATOR — DECODED

Built by @howrie in PineScript v5. Three layers:

### Layer 1 — Volume Engine
- Pulls 5-minute buying volume regardless of chart timeframe
- Buying volume = volume on bullish candles only (close > open)
- Measures cumulative increase over last 12 bars (1 hour on 5m feed) vs 20-period SMA
- Volume cross fires when sustained buying exceeds the average

### Layer 2 — RSI States
- 14-period RSI
- RSI crossing ABOVE 80 + volume cross = GREEN TRIANGLE (momentum acceleration — NOT just overbought)
- RSI sustained BELOW 20 + volume cross = RED TRIANGLE (can fire multiple times during capitulation)
- RSI > 50 = uptrend mode | RSI ≤ 50 = downtrend mode

### Layer 3 — Percentile Forecast Band
- Stores last 50 bars of price movement relative to trend start
- When RSI crosses 50 — replays ALL historical instances of similar trend changes
- BLUE band = uptrend forecast (RSI crossed above 50) — BE LONG
- RED/PINK band = downtrend forecast (RSI crossed below 50) — BE CAUTIOUS/SHORT
- Band width = uncertainty (wider = more volatile history)
- Mid line = 50th percentile (median expected path)
- **RESETS every time RSI crosses 50** — this is the master signal

### Key Rules From Howrie Logic
- Green triangle = BOTH volume cross AND RSI crossing 80 simultaneously — momentum confirmation
- Multiple red triangles during oversold = CAPITULATION signal (smart money buying)
- Blue band + RSI above 50 = hold longs
- Red band switch = EXIT signal regardless of price action
- Volume fade (blue fill under candles) = accumulation detector — brighter = stronger buying

